content:
Create a Data Category Group

Data categories offer an alternative type of categorization for catalog items. Organizing catalog items under a data category makes those catalog items viewable on LWR sites.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions
From Setup, enter Service Catalog, select Catalog Settings.
On the Catalog Categorization Method dropdown, select Data Categories.
Click Categories Builder.
Create a new data category group by clicking New.
Enter a name and description for your data category group.
Click Save.

Your new data category group is saved in an inactive state. Activate it to add sibling or child categories.
Add sibling or child categories before or after activating.
Save your work.

Edit, delete, or deactivate created data category groups and data categories within them. If deleting a data category with items, reassign those items to another category. Catalog items without a category appear in Catalog Management.

Salesforce Help: Work With Data Categories
title: Creating and Managing Service Cloud Data Category Groups
